# Cursor AI Rules for IB Bot Project

## Documentation & Summaries
- **NO summary documents**: NEVER create summary, results, or completion documents (e.g., SUMMARY.md, CHANGES_SUMMARY.md, FINAL_SUMMARY.md, RESULTS.md, IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md, etc.)
- **NO automatic documentation**: Do not create README files, guide files, or documentation files unless explicitly requested by the user
- Provide brief summaries directly in chat responses only
- Only create documentation files when the user specifically asks for them
- Focus on code and functionality, not documentation

## Code Style
- Follow existing code patterns in the project
- Use clear, descriptive variable names
- Add docstrings for public methods

## Security
- NEVER hardcode secrets, passwords, API keys, or TOTP codes in source files
- All secrets go in `.env` (gitignored) and are read via `app.core.config.Settings`
- API endpoints (except `/health`, `/docs`) are protected by `API_KEY` middleware when configured
- Rate limiting is enforced via shared `app.core.limiter.limiter` -- import from there, do not create new `Limiter` instances
- When adding new sensitive endpoints, add tighter `@limiter.limit()` decorators

## Testing
- Run verification after major changes
- Use existing test files in the project
- 3 test files have pre-existing import errors (repo-root modules not on path): `test_edgar_13f_fallback.py`, `test_plot_data_cache.py`, `test_rebalancing_engine_regressions.py` -- skip with `--ignore` when running locally
- Rate limiting is auto-disabled in test fixtures via `limiter.enabled = False` in conftest.py
